<h2>Modify/Add Auto Responder</h2>
<div class="filthypillow"></div>

<p>When configuring an auto responder, you can use the following tags to insert information into the response email:</p>
<span class="bold">^S</span>
<p>The subject of the message sent to the auto responder.</p>
<span class="bold">^F</span>
<p>From address of the original message (decoded, converted to UTF-8, including the \"Real name\" part).</p>
<span class="bold">^E</span>
<p>The incoming email senderâ€™s address only.</p>
<div class="form-group">
  <label for="email">Email</label>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
      <div class="input-group">
	<select id="email" class="form-control">
	  <% for (var a = 0; a < accounts.length; a++) { %>
	     <% if ( accounts[a] != "pbx" && accounts[a] != "ivr" ) { %>
	     <option <% if(autoresponder && autoresponder.email.split('@')[0] == accounts[a]) { %>selected<% } %> ><%= accounts[a] %></option>
	     <% } %>
	  <% } %>
	</select>
        <span class="input-group-addon">@</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-6" id="email_error"></div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="form-group">
  <label for="domain">Domain</label>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4 col-md-4 col-lg-4">
      <select id="domain" class="form-control">
	<% for (var i = 0; i < domains.length; i++) { %>
	<option <% if(domains[i].domain == domain) { %>selected<% } %> ><%= domains[i].domain %></option>
	<% } %>
      </select>
    </div>
    <span id="domain-loading" style="line-height: 35px; margin-left: 10px;"></span>
  </div>
</div>

